Description: Signed and unsigned 8-bit (1 byte) integer types
Standard single-precision floating point; compatible with C float
Standard double-precision floating point; compatible with C double and Python float object
Complex numbers represented by two 32, 64, or 128 floats, respectively
Boolean type storing True and False values
Python object type; a value can be any Python object
Fixed-length ASCII string type (1 byte per character); for example, to create a string dtype with length 10, use 'S10'
Fixed-length Unicode type (number of bytes platform specific); same specification semantics as string_ (e.g., 'U10')
